Sentencas: SrCoO3-delta,5 is a mixed ionic-electronic conductor with multiphase.
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The structural instability, chemical and thermal incompatibility with the standard electrolytes in this material restrict its widespread applications as electrochemical devices.
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Here we report the characterization and performance improvement of SrCo0.8Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-delta (SCFN) perovskite as a potential cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SCFN material exhibits good chemical compatibility with both La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (LSGM) and Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95 (GDC) electrolytes at 950 degrees C for 10 h. Fe and Nb co-doping significantly improves the structural stability, thermal expansion compatibility, and electrochemical performance of the SCFN material as compared to the undoped SrCoO3-delta,, and Fe-doped SrCo0.8Fe0.2Nb0.1O3-delta (SCF).
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introduction of GDC further improves the thermal compatibility and electrochemical performance of the SCFN GDC composite cathodes, where the thermal expansion coefficients decrease from 24.5 x 10(-6) K-1 for SCFN to 16.8 x 10(-6) K-1 for SCFN-50GDC between 30 and 950 degrees C in air, the corresponding area specific resistances are 0.091 and 0.075 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SCFN and its composites reveal some promising aspects of applications in IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The SCFN GDC composites provide a trade-off between TEC and electrochemical performance for application as IT-SOFC cathode materials.
Titulo: Stability, compatibility and performance improvement of SrCo0.9Fe0.1Nb0.1O3-δ perovskite as a cathode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
